<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>ADP<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Automatic Data Processing Inc. — mathematically derived from current data.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated Today</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice.toFixed(2)} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(currentRev / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Recent Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(baseFcf / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${epsArray[0]?.toFixed(2) || 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{sharesOutstanding}M</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Shares Outstanding</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — projecting cash flows mathematically derived from ADP's historical performance, rather than fabricated inputs.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Base Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>ADP generated <strong>${baseFcf.toLocaleString()} million</strong> in free cash flow recently. This serves as our starting base for projection.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Phase 1 Growth Projection</h4>
      <p>We project FCF growth at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong> for the next 5 years. This rate is derived from an average of ADP's 4-year Free Cash Flow CAGR and 4-year Revenue CAGR, providing a balanced blend of top-line and bottom-line trends.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Terminal Value (Gordon Growth)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assign a mature, terminal growth rate of <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong>. This models a perpetual, steady state for a stable payroll compounder, staying slightly below historical GDP growth.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount Cash Flows to Present</h4>
      <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong>. We calculated this required rate of return using a 10Y Treasury yield of 4.18%, an estimated beta of 0.82, and an equity risk premium of 5.0%.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Final Equity Value</h4>
      <p>We add Enterprise Value to Net Cash (Cash & Equivalents minus Total Debt), arriving at the Equity Value. Dividing this by diluted shares outstanding gives our intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>Core Assumptions</h2>
  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Phase 1 FCF Growth</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Calculated by taking the average of ADP's 4-year historical Revenue CAGR ({(revCagr * 100).toFixed(1)}%) and FCF CAGR ({(fcfCagr * 100).toFixed(1)}%). We capped extremes to reflect reasonable, sustainable future growth.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Derived mathematically via CAPM: Risk-Free Rate (4.18%) + Beta (0.82) × Equity Risk Premium (5.0%). Rounded to the nearest half-percent for model stability.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Mature, structural growth expected for ADP's established HCM and payroll services, roughly keeping pace with long-term inflation and GDP expectations.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
