  <!-- ═══ SENSITIVITY ANALYSIS ═══ -->
  <h2>Sensitivity Analysis</h2>
  <p>Intrinsic value is highly dependent on discount and growth rates. Observe how the intrinsic value shifts under slightly different inputs.</p>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table class="sensitivity-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Discount Rate ↓ / Growth →</th>
          {sensitivityGrowth.map(g => (
            <th class={Math.abs(g - baseGr) < 0.001 ? 'current' : ''}>{(g * 100).toFixed(1)}%</th>
          ))}
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {sensitivityTable.map(row => (
          <tr>
            <td>{(row.dr * 100).toFixed(1)}%</td>
            {row.values.map((v, i) => (
              <td class={(Math.abs(row.dr - baseDr) < 0.001) && (Math.abs(sensitivityGrowth[i] - baseGr) < 0.001) ? 'current' : ''}>
                ${v}
              </td>
            ))}
          </tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ RISKS ═══ -->
  <h2>Model Risks</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Macroeconomic Sensitivity:</strong> ADP's growth is tied to employment levels. A severe recession could lower both headcount and interest earned on client funds.</li>
    <li><strong>Interest Rates:</strong> ADP benefits from higher rates through float income (funds held for clients). Declining rates could hamper margin expansion.</li>
    <li><strong>Competition:</strong> Disruption from agile, cloud-native HR and payroll software providers (like Workday, Paycom, Rippling) could erode pricing power.</li>
  </ul>

