  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq">
    <details>
      <summary>Why is ADP's float income important?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">ADP holds client funds before paying them out as payroll or taxes. They earn interest on this massive "float" — acting somewhat like a bank. Higher interest rates significantly boost this zero-cost revenue stream.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>How resilient is ADP's free cash flow?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Historically, ADP has very robust and predictable cash generation due to strong client retention and the critical, recurring nature of payroll services.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Is this a buy recommendation?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">No. This is an educational analytical framework to estimate fair value based on mathematical projections of historical data. Always perform independent due diligence.</div>
    </details>
